rComments: many tests but they are easy if you did your home work and dgds since he puts the same kind of questions. He is organised and knows his stuff,overall great teacher :)
Very good teacher, knows his stuff and doesn't surprise during tests :)

While taking your phone out during class is a death sentence, his lectures were among the most interesting I've had at OttawaU. He makes it clear what you need to prepare for in the DGDs, and while the earlier tests seemed like material that wasn't covered in class towards the end you learn how to prepare for them.

He was not a bad teacher, but his teaching technique seemed... wrong. I found him rude; I had the expression he was mocking us sometimes. He hates cellphones, and won't mind shaming you in front of everyone if you take it out.
The  teacher hate  cellPhone and laptop ,The DGD aren't  helpful ,need a personnal work , he have a good french ,the course is ok.

Always ready to answer your questions DURING class, so no need really to see him during his office hours.  Toujours prêt a répondre aux questions durant le cours, donc tu n'as pas besoin de lui voir durant ses heures de bureaux.

Very good prof. Explains things well and is dynamic. He really doesn't like laptops, cell-phones, etc..., so don't use them! His site has a bunch of old testexams, which really come in helpful and he posts all his notes online along with another profs' notes. Also, seeing as linear algebra isn't always the easiest subject - hard work is needed.

Not a bad teacher, but I hate asking questions in class because he seems to laugh at you (in his office hours, he is ok...). Often late. It's great that his notes are on his website, but his examples are all the same!Plus, in his exams, there are things we never saw! By the way, don't even think about texting if you don't want your head on a stake.
This is a great  teacher. I don't think the other comments  give an honest description of the class.  There is a lot of content on-line , and he is clear when he explains .

Great prof, his tests are exactly like what we did in our DGDs, so make sure to attend  classes and review everything. It's great because has a website where he posts all the class notes. Definitely take this class with him if you can!  Excellent prof! Prenez ce cours avec lui si vous pouvez,  et assurez vous d'aller a tous ces coursDGD.

He's not very clear, but it's an easy class. The DGD's are really important!!! We had tests every other week and a final which is a good thing !!!! Don't touch your phone, tablet or laptop in class is you don't want to be yelled at. No textbook required, he started writing the notes on the board but after 2-3 weeks he started posting them online.
I'm going to make this comment as clear as he would say. First of all don't even think about taking your pone out in class. Secondly if you don't show up you will suffer in the tests and exams.

Where do I start... He has really bad hand writing and writes incredibly small. He only writes the book description of complex concepts, assumes you know everything already and either raises his voice or mocks you if you ask a question. Notes not available online. Doesn't provide any suggested problems for upcoming exams. You need a tutor to pass.
